comments: Suggs (ORL) fails to fully clear the lane and is in the paint for longer than three seconds without imminently actively guarding an opponent.
During the rebound, Wagner (ORL) and Aldridge (BKN) mutually engage and disengage and the contact is marginal.
Suggs (ORL) cleanly deflects the rebound away from Aldridge (BKN) and is the last to touch the ball before it goes out of bounds.
Aldridge (BKN) and Wagner (ORL) mutually engage and disengage off ball and marginal contact occurs as they jostle for post position.
Suggs (ORL) is in the paint for longer than three seconds without imminently actively guarding an opponent.
Bamba (ORL) reaches for the ball and marginal contact occurs with Johnson (BKN), which does not affect his ability to secure the rebound.
Aldridge (BKN) turns toward the basket and marginal contact occurs with Wagner (ORL) as they come together in the post.
Suggs (ORL) is in the paint for less than three seconds when he is imminently actively guarding an opponent.
Johnson (BKN) has a resting hand on Anthony's (ORL) back, which he does not extend or deliver contact with during the driving shot attempt.
Anthony (ORL) briefly grasps Johnson's (BKN) vertical arm to create the marginal contact after the release on his driving shot attempt.
Suggs (ORL) is in the paint for less than three seconds when he is imminently actively guarding an opponent.

Suggs (ORL) extends his arm toward the ball and marginal contact occurs with Harden's (BKN) head, which does not affect his ability to make his intended pass.  Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
Wagner (ORL) absorbs the contact and marginal contact occurs as he slides his hands off of Aldridge (BKN) in the post.
Wagner (ORL) makes clean ball contact to deflect the post entry pass away from Aldridge (BKN).
Suggs (ORL) is in the paint for less than three seconds when he is imminently actively guarding an opponent.
Harden (BKN) commits a take foul on Ross (ORL).
Harden (BKN) and Ross (ORL) engage and disengage and marginal contact occurs as he receives the inbounds pass.
Harden (BKN) commits a take foul on Ross (ORL).
Before Suggs (ORL) gets his hand on the ball, Wagner (ORL) swipes down and makes contact to Harden's (BKN) arm that affects his control of the ball.
Johnson (BKN) moves alongside of Suggs (ORL) and absorbs the contact as he brings his arm into a vertical position to contest the play at the basket.
Wagner (ORL) commits a take foul on Harden (BKN).
Carter (BKN) commits a take foul on Anthony (ORL).
Carter Jr. (ORL) and Griffin (BKN) mutually engage and disengage and marginal contact occurs as they jostle for potential rebounding position, before the free throw violation is whistled.
Anthony's (ORL) free throw attempt does not touch the rim and a free throw violation is correctly called.
Aldridge (BKN) establishes himself in a screening position in Suggs' (ORL) path and absorbs the contact during the screen.
Anthony (ORL) extends his arms out and marginal contact occurs with Harden (BKN) after he releases his pass.
